<subSubSection pageId="192" pageNumber="795" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="192.[1984,2578,987,1431]" pageId="192" pageNumber="795">
A morphological and molecular study by P. Chevret and colleagues in 2003 confirmed its position in the subgenus Pyromys, where it is sister to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bennett" authorityYear="1832" box="[2174,2345,1201,1235]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="192" pageNumber="795" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platythrix">M. platythrix</taxonomicName>
. Previously considered a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bennett" authorityYear="1832" box="[2303,2474,1240,1274]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Mus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="192" pageNumber="795" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platythrix">M. platythrix</taxonomicName>
. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
